results.name: Number of 5's in decimal expansion of prime(n).
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
program: count5 c x | d == 5    = if x < 10 then c + 1 else count5 (c + 1) x'
| otherwise = if x < 10 then c else count5 c x'
